            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick, with a matching lid) over medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>pak choi leaves</strong>, <strong>spring onion thirds </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook, covered, for 3-4 min or until both have softened</p><p>Once softened, add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and<strong> toasted sesame oil</strong> and cook for 1 min further – this is your <strong>sesame pak choi & spring onions</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1701856194297-x200.jpg",
